From Leigh Palmer Subject Re Orion drive in vacuum how In article James Goltz goltz writes Background The Orion spacedrive was a theoretical It was more than a theoretical concept it was seriously pursued by Freeman Dyson et al many years I don't know how well known this is but a high explosive Orion prototype flew in the atmosphere in San Diego back in or I was working at General Atomic at the time but I didn't learn about the experiment until almost thirty years later when Ted Taylor visited us and revealed that it had been I feel sure that someone must have film of that experiment and I'd really like to see Has anyone out there seen it Leigh